Set Up Your Data in SageMaker

Access Salesforce data in an Amazon SageMaker notebook using a Python connector. The user-friendly interface helps you to quickly execute queries against Data Cloud so you can extract the data that you need into Python.

In your SageMaker notebook, install the CDP Python Connector. The connector enables you to access Data Cloud objects and ingest Salesforce data into SageMaker.
As part of the Python connector configuration, create a connected app.
Authenticate to securely access your data using one of these methods.
Key-based
JWT
In Data Cloud, connect to your Salesforce data source to query the dataset. For example, to get your email engagement data, access the Email Engagement object in Marketing Cloud Engagement.
To consume the inferences in Data Cloud, upload the Python file to your notebook.
To get your model endpoint, go to the SageMaker dashboard in the Inferences section, and go to Endpoints. Note the URL as you need these details to connect your model with Salesforce.
